HEADWORD: Frostwork
<hw>Frost`work"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The figurework,
often fantastic and delicate, which moisture sometimes forms in
freezing, as upon a window pane or a flagstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frostwort</ent>⟦br⟧
